OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1781021474
OL,3,CThousands of doctors to walk out in
OL,4,Ctwo-day strike over pay
OL,6,FThe British Medical Association (BMA)
OL,7,Fsaid that 92% of it's resident doctors
OL,8,Fand 79% of consultants voted for
OL,9,Fstrike action.
OL,11,FThe BMA said it is "now renewing its
OL,12,Fcalls for the health minister to
OL,13,Furgently engage with the organisation
OL,14,Fand avoid strikes with a credible pay
OL,15,Foffer."
OL,17,FThe disagreement between the
OL,18,Fdepartment and BMA is primarily due to
OL,19,Flong-standing dispute over pay
OL,20,Ferosion, workforce retention and late
OL,21,For unguaranteed pay awards.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/7
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1781021474
OL,3,CThousands of doctors to walk out in
OL,4,Ctwo-day strike over pay
OL,6,FIt follows the rejection by BMA
OL,7,Fmembers of a 3.5% pay uplift
OL,8,Frecommended by the UK government's
OL,9,FReview Body on Doctors' and Dentists'
OL,10,FRemuneration (DDRB). The BMA said it
OL,11,Frepresented a real-terms pay cut when
OL,12,Fweighed against inflation.
OL,14,FHealth Minister Mike Nesbitt said he
OL,15,Fwas "disappointed" by the ballot and
OL,16,Fadded that he is "committed to
OL,17,Fimplementing this year's pay award,
OL,18,Fbut is currently unable to do so in
OL,19,Fthe absence of an Executive agreed
OL,20,Fbudget."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/7
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1781021474
OL,3,CThousands of doctors to walk out in
OL,4,Ctwo-day strike over pay
OL,6,FThe minister also warned about
OL,7,Ffinancial pressures on the health
OL,8,Fbudget saying: "While the Department
OL,9,Fwill continue to engage with health
OL,10,Funions, we must recognise that the
OL,11,Ffinancial constraints within which we
OL,12,Fare operating mean there is no room
OL,13,Ffor movement beyond the 3.5%
OL,14,Frecommended by DDRB."
OL,16,FThe first 24 hour strike is due to be
OL,17,Ftaken by consultants on Thursday June
OL,18,F25. The planned action will see a
OL,19,FChristmas Day-style cover model, with
OL,20,Femergency services continuing, but
OL,21,Froutine work heavily disrupted.
OL,26,@pD@POUvD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/7
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
